Privacy Policy – Clinical Repertory Pro (Atlorep)
Last Updated: November 23, 2025

Clinical Repertory Pro (also known as “Atlorep”) is a medical educational application developed and maintained by Nideesh Srihass M K S. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect the personal information of our users.

1. Developer Information
Developer: Nideesh Srihass M K S
Official Email: srihass@camoratechnologies.com
Website: https://camoratechnologies.com/pages/index
Address:
Dr. Seethapathy Nagar South Extn,
Velachery, Chennai – 600042,
Tamil Nadu, India.

2. Information We Collect
Login information: Username and password (stored safely and not shared).
Saved case data: Topics, symptoms, and notes you save inside the app (stored only on your device).
Crash & performance data: Automatically collected to improve the app.
3. What We Do Not Collect
No Aadhaar / PAN / ID numbers
No photos, contacts, SMS, call logs, or location
No real patient medical records
No financial information
4. How We Use Your Information
To manage login and membership access
To generate repertory analysis
To improve performance and fix issues
To provide customer support
5. Payments
All membership payments are processed exclusively through Google Play Billing. We do not collect or store any card, UPI, or banking information.

6. Data Security
We implement strong security measures including local encryption, obfuscated code, and secure access control. No user data is transmitted to external servers unless explicitly required.

7. Children’s Privacy
This app is intended for users aged 18 and above. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.

8. Third-Party Services
We only use trusted Google Play services for crash reporting, analytics, and payments.

9. Your Rights
You may request clarification or deletion of local data at any time by contacting us at srihass@camoratechnologies.com.

10. Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this privacy policy, please contact:
Nideesh Srihass M K S
Email: srihass@camoratechnologies.com
